article.description: Anthony Brown returned a strip-sack 17 yards for a touchdown and UT Martin used five turnovers to beat Eastern Illinois 27-10 on Saturday.
article.headline: UT Martin forces 5 turnovers in 27-10 win over E. Illinois
article.linkText: UT Martin forces 5 turnovers in 27-10 win over E. Illinois
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Anthony Brown returned a strip-sack 17 yards for a touchdown and UT Martin used five turnovers to beat Eastern Illinois 27-10 on Saturday. UT Martin scored 17 points off those turnovers. Brown's score made it 10-3. Four plays later, Tae Martin returned an interception 42 yards and Troy Cook connected with Donnell Williams for a 1-yard score. Kahlid Hagens set up the Brown's TD with a sack and Hagens' 6-yard interception return ended Eastern Illinois' final drive of the first half. James Gilleylen returned an interception 27 yards, leading to a field goal for a 27-10 lead, and Andrew Horton-Martindale made UT Martin's fourth interception. UT Martin (4-4, 2/3 Ohio Valley Conference) only attempted 12 passes and gained 80 yards on 39 carries. Bud Martin threw for 155 yards and three interceptions for Eastern Illinois (5-4, 4-2), which outgained UT Martin 275 yards to 192. --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
